[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'What if you could capture a moment not as a flat video, but as a living 3D scene you could walk around inside? That\'s what Gaussian splatting does. It takes video of a subject from many angles at once and rebuilds it as a soft'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cloud of millions of 3D points, a fully dimensional record of reality. You can fly through it, pause in midair, replay'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it from any viewpoint. It\'s how we get voluuttric sports replays, digital doubles for film, and XR worlds you can move through. But there\'s a catch. To'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rebuild a scene in 3D, you have to capture every angle at the exact same instant, which has always meant a permanent studio. Dozens of wired'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cameras, racks of computers, hours of manual work before a single clip is usable. Meridian changes that. It\'s a fully untethered batterypowered volutric'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stage. An entire studio in a flight case. One portable frame. 56 iPhone 17 Pro cameras synced to fire in perfect'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lock step with built-in image-based lighting. No cables, no external power, no hours of processing.'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Each iPhone shoots 4K ProRes RAW and acts as its own computer, trimming, coloring, and uploading on device every camera at once.'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'What took a studio and a day now takes one step. And here\'s the breakthrough. You don\'t bring the world to the stage. You bring the stage to the world.'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Meridian deploys anywhere on Earth the same day, capturing reality where the story actually happens. The stadium, the street, the moment itself.'

[02:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Radiant images Images Meridian reality in every dimension.'
